Package org.scec.param.editor

Interface Summary
ParameterEditorAPI Title: ParameterEditorAPI
Description: All Parameter Editors must implement these functions so that the Parameter Editor knows how to handle them without knowing the exact Editor class it is dealing with.

Class Summary
ConstrainedDoubleDiscreteParameterEditor Title: ConstrainedDoubleDiscreteParameterEditor
Description: This editor is for editing DoubleDiscreteParameter.
ConstrainedDoubleParameterEditor Title: ConstrainedDoubleParameterEditor
Description: Special ParameterEditor for editing Constrained DoubleParameters.
ConstrainedIntegerParameterEditor Title: ConstrainedIntegerParameterEditor
Description: Special ParameterEditor for editing IntegetParameters.
ConstrainedStringParameterEditor Title: ConstrainedStringParameterEditor
Description: This editor is for editing ConstrainedStringParameter.
DoubleParameterEditor Title: DoubleParameterEditor
Description: Special ParameterEditor for editing DoubleParameters.
IntegerParameterEditor Title: IntegerParameterEditor
Description: Special ParameterEditor for editing IntegetParameters.
IntegerTextField Title: IntegerTextField
Description: Special JTextField that only allows integers to be typed in.
NumericTextField Title: NumericTextField
Description: Special JTextField that only allows numbers to be typed in.
ParameterEditor Title: ParameterEditor
Description: This is the base Editor class that all Editors extend from This sets up a JPanel to have a Label on the left, cooresponding to the name of the Parameter, and a widget on the right.
ParameterEditorFactory Title: ParameterEditorFactory
Description: This factory is used to create the appropiate Editor for a Parameter based on the String type.
ParameterListEditor Title: ParameterListEditor
Description: The main Parameter Editor Panel that takes in a ParameterList, and using the ParameterEditorFactory to build all individual Parameter Editors for each editor in the Parameter List.
StringParameterEditor Title: StringParameterEditor
Description: Simplist Editor in that the widget is a JTExtField with no Constraints on it.
